The ‘Itala recensio,' based in the last twelve plays upon D, seems in the earlier plays to have been based on a MS. that exhibited this ‘doctored' text. All Renaissance MSS. oi Plautus are therefore of no valae whatsoever as evidence for the text of Plautus, whether in the first eight or in the last twelve plays.
